snippet.textDisplay: I honestly don’t understand why people are so upset over Disney remaking Mulan. The story of mulan you all love is far from the real folklore of mulan, In Asia the Disney animated movie flopped because of historical inaccuracy and made the real mulan story into a girl fighting for her father and then falling in love, there was no dragon and no singing. Mulan was about basically women empowerment and how women can be strong amongst men. And yes Disney did add a witch to add to the plot, to make the movie more interesting, now stop complaint and appreciate that Disney is trying to make it different from a love story.

snippet.textDisplay: Does it bother anyone else that they felt the need to add a female villain? The whole point is that Mulan can not only hold her own, but excel in a war of men. This witch character seems to exist only so Mulan can fight with another girl while the men just fight each other. I worry that the original main villain will be defeated by someone else while Mulan takes on the witch, segregating the war by gender and suggesting that she could only fight another girl and couldn't take on men. I have no problem with a reimaging, but I would rather they have taken magic out entirely and gone for war epic than this.
